Day 6:
Step 0: Log in to the Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com/).


______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Create Point to Site on Azure, A Point-to-Site (P2S) VPN gateway lets you create a secure connection to your virtual network from an individual computer:

Step 1: Create a Virtual Network.
Step 2: Cnfigure the Vnet by providing Vnet name, Resource Group, and location.
Step 3: Create a Gateway Subnet.
Step 4: Create a Virtual Network Gateway.
Step 5: Configure the Virtual Network Gateway by selecting appropriate Subscription, Resource Group and Vnet.
Step 6: Generate a root certificate.
Step 7: Download the VPN ckient.
Step 8: Install the VPN client on client machines.
Step 9: Connect to Vnet.
Step 10: Verify the connection.


